{
  "texts": [
    "The third stage of the V-SLAM workflow focuses on the crucial task of building the map, an essential element in V-SLAM processes.",
    "Various types of maps can be generated using SLAM, including topological maps, volumetric (3D) maps, such as point cloud and occupancy grid maps, and feature-based or landmark maps.",
    "The choice of the map type is based on factors such as the sensors employed, application requirements, environmental assumptions, and the type of dataset used in robotic applications (Taheri and Xia, 2021; Fernández-Moral et al., 2013).",
    "In robotics, a grid map is a representation of a physical environment, with each cell representing a particular location and storing data comprising obstacles, topography, and occupancy.",
    "It functions as a fundamental data structure for several robotics navigation and localization techniques (Grisetti et al., 2007)."
  ]
}